Merge pull request #40 from facebook/wbailey

API improvements

API improvements

- Springs with no tension continue to move when velocity is applied
  until friction causes them to stop if no end value is set.
- setCurrentValue now performs setAtRest by default with a new method
  signature added to support the uncommon use-case of setting current
  value without setting at rest

Internal Cleanup

- Combine SpringClock with looper
- Add SynchronousLooper for doing synchronous simulation
- Add SteppingLooper for doing step by step simulation
- pull in hamcrest for testing and update tests
- activateSpring on velocity or currentValue changed
- bump version

Merge pull request #37 from facebook/bugfix

Convert ReentrantCallback to CopyOnWriteArraySet

Convert ReentrantCallback to CopyOnWriteArraySet

This fixes a ConcurrentModificationException that can be caused by
adding/removing listeners while iterating. This arose when the
ReentrantCallback code was modified to avoid using Guava and
UnmodifiableSet was incorrectly used as a replacement for ImmutableSet.
UnmodifiableSet allows the underlying collection to be modified which
leads to the exception if performed during iteration. This should be
faster as well and removes some custom code.
Use setImmediate instead of nextTick in node
